<dl id="n26266i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n26" href="#n26266i">N26 (VI.B.18)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n26all.htm#n26266i"> 266(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> lares / manes / penates <small>Green</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n26266i"><li>FW 179.10 </li><li><a href="../../flex/g/lexg.htm#n26266i">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/g/l39g.htm#n26266i">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n26266i">MS BL 47474-76v</ms> </li><li>JJA 47:475 <a name="gd7" href="../../ff/fdra/gda.htm#gd7">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/g/gd7.htm#n26266i">Draft: I.7&sect;1.7</a>/2.7</li> </ul> <ul class="list-inline" id="n26266i"></li><li>FW 432.14 </li><li><a href="../../flex/qA/lexqA.htm#n26266i">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/qA/l39qA.htm#n26266i">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n26266i">MS VI.F.6-3</ms> </li><li>JJA not reproduced <a name="qAd10dash" href="../../ff/fdra/qda.htm#qAd10dash">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/qA/qAd10.htm#n26266i">Draft: III&sect;2A.10</a>'</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Institutions of the Private Law. Domestic relations]</font>&mdash;The husband was priest in his family, but wife and children alike assisted in its prayers, and took part in the sacrifices to its <mark>lares and penates</mark> <font color="green">[household gods]</font>. As the Greek called his wife the house-mistress, &delta;&epsilon;&pi;&omicron;&iota;&nu;&alpha;, so did the Roman speak of his as <i>materfamilias</i>, the house-mother <font color="green">[the woman of the house]</font>. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> 535&mdash;To avenge the death of a kinsman was more than a right; it was a religious duty, for his <mark><i>manes</i></mark> <font color="green">[ghost]</font> had to be appeased. <small> &ldquo;ROMAN LAW&rdquo; <a name="EBRL2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBRL2"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 530</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also <a name="n21002b" href="n21all.htm#n21002b">N21 (VI.B.20):002(b)</a></mm> </dd></dl>
